1 Self-assessments completed mainly by suppliers from non-OECD countries with a purchasing volume of > €50,000 per year. Questionnaires that were initiated, completed, and concluded in the reporting period.

2 Commonwealth of Independent States. 3

Improvement measures agreed on with suppliers relate either to actual deviations from the Supplier Code of Conduct, structural improvements in management systems, or a lack of specific processes and guidelines implemented by the supplier.

3.3 Sustainable supply chain practices

External sustainability audits From our perspective, external sustainability audits are the

most effective means of evaluating our suppliers’ sustain- ability performance. These audits are conducted by our external audit service provider and serve as a control mechanism for suppliers identified as high-risk.